Tom Huddlestone believes the Tottenham Hotspur revolution on Humberside will help Hull City cement their place as a Premier League club.

Michael Dawson became the third player to swap White Hart Lane for the KC Stadium this week when he joined in a £3.5 million deal.

That trio — Dawson, Huddlestone and Jake Livermore — have all been capped by England and cost the Tigers a combined £15m.

