The midfielder — a £5.25m arrival last summer — added: ‘I saw potential in the squad last year which made me sign and we had a good season, which is attracting players like Dawson and Abel Hernandez [the Uruguay striker on the verge of a £10m move from Palermo].

‘The season we had last year is helping bring quality players like that and long may it continue. We’ve made a statement with these signings.’

Hull are in their second season in the top flight under the canny guidance of Steve Bruce. They were FA Cup finalists in May but failed to progress to the Europa League group stage after exiting on away goals to Belgian side Sporting Lokeren on Thursday.

‘The lads are devastated,’ Huddlestone admitted. ‘We obviously won the game but away goals are cruel. Seeing the Europa League draw was when it fully sunk in.

